This paper is primarily focused on generating images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of scene graphs and graph convolution also suggests a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in generative models and falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of bounding boxes and segmentation masks, which are common tools in graphics (cs.GR).
